.TH COWSAY(1),User Commands,COWSAY(1)

.SH NAME
cowsay - print a message as ASCII art spoken by a cow

.SH SYNOPSIS
cowsay [-l] [-w width] [-h] [message ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
cowsay prints a speech bubble containing the given message,
followed by an ASCII-art cow pointing at the bubble.

If no message is given on the command line, cowsay reads the message from standard input.
Input read from stdin is split into words at newlines.

Message words are flowed across multiple lines as needed to fit within the bubble width.

.SH OPTIONS
-w width: Set the maximum bubble width in characters.
The default is 40.

-l: Literal mode.
Print each argument on its own line instead of flowing words across lines.

-h: Print a short usage summary and exit 0.

.SH EXAMPLES
$ cowsay hello world

$ cowsay -w 20 the quick brown fox

$ echo "moo" | cowsay

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: Message printed.

1: Option -w was given without a width argument.
